This paper is about face attribute prediction using a novel multi-task neural network. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks related to facial attributes, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new neural network architecture, which involves sharing low-level features and splitting high-level features, and uses a novel tensor correlation analysis algorithm. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also uses benchmarks with multiple face attributes, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves fine-tuning subnetworks and making predictions based on a correlation matrix, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
